The paper deals with generating and validating logical proofs, which is a topic that falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of automated theorem proving, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the design of a calculus, which is a topic in programming languages (cs.PL). The transformation of computational steps into logic proofs involves data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and the application of the proof generation to the Kepler Conjecture involves scientific computing (cs.SC).
